text: The Pangasinan people, (Pangasinan: "mga Pangasinense") are one of the northern Philippine hilitribal group particularly in northern Luzon, it has a similar related of most Ilocanos locality from Ilocos provinces and the Kapampangan situated at the southern portion in Pangasinan.https://warren913.wordpress.com/culture-and-its-people The northern portion of Zambales province and the western portion of Nueva Vizcaya are Pangasinan speakers.https://dbpedia.org/page/Pangasinan_people ==Reference== Category:Ethnic groups in the Philippines
title: Pangasinan people
